The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Wednesday, September 28, 2005

 School awards

 The Telegraph School Awards for Excellence 2005 at Science City, 9.30 am. Infosys chief mentor N.R. Narayan Murthy will be the chief guest. By invitation only.

 Poetry

 A poetry-reading session as part of fringe poetry festival, The Urban Beat, organised by Oxford Bookstore and Kalam: Margins Write, at the bookstore, 6.30 pm.

 On stage

 A recital by vocalist Purnima Sen at ITC Sangeet Research Academy, 6 pm.

 A programme of folk dance, organised by Spicmacay, at BD Memorial School, 2.30 pm.

 Talk

 A talk by Margaret McDonell from Australia on ?Challenges of Cross-Cultural Writing? at Srijan?s rooftop, 6 pm to 8 pm.

 In camera

 An exhibition of photographs by Benoy Behl to celebrate World Tourism Day at Asutosh Mukherjee Birth Centenary Hall, Indian Museum, 11 am to 7 pm.

 Exhibition

 Ready-to-wear, textiles, jewellery, artworks, books and decor items on view at CIMA Gallery, 11 am to 8 pm.

 Paintings at GC Laha Centenary Fine Arts Gallery, 1 pm to 7 pm.

 An exhibition of cotton and silk saris, yardage, dupattas and stoles at Tvastr, Swabhumi, noon to 8 pm.




